  "prompt": "What is the healthiest food I can snack on throughout the day? Must be fairly affordable + fairly tasty.",
  "response": "There are several healthy, affordable, and tasty snack options you can consider. Here are some of the best:\n\n1. **Fresh Fruits**: Apples, bananas, oranges, and berries are often affordable. They\u2019re nutritious, portable, and naturally sweet.\n\n2. **Vegetable Sticks with Hummus**: Carrots, cucumber, and bell peppers cut into sticks are great for dipping. Hummus is a healthy and tasty option that is also easy to make at home.\n\n3. **Greek Yogurt**: Look for plain Greek yogurt, which is high in protein and can be sweetened with fresh fruit or a drizzle of honey.\n\n4. **Nuts and Seeds**: Almonds, walnuts, sunflower seeds, and pumpkin seeds are nutrient-dense and satisfying. Just be mindful of portion sizes, as they can be calorie-dense.\n\n5. **Popcorn**: Air-popped popcorn is a whole grain and can be a healthy snack if you don't load it up with too much butter or salt.\n\n6. **Whole Grain Crackers or Rice Cakes with Avocado**: Spread some mashed avocado on whole grain crackers or rice cakes for a healthy, tasty treat.\n\n7. **Cottage Cheese**: A good source of protein, cottage cheese can be paired with fruits, nuts, or honey for added flavor.\n\n8. **Hard-Boiled Eggs**: These are an excellent source of protein and can be prepared in advance for easy snacking.\n\n9. **Homemade Trail Mix**: Combine nuts, seeds, dried fruits, and a few dark chocolate chips for a tasty and healthy snack.\n\n10. **Dark Chocolate**: A small piece of dark chocolate can satisfy your sweet tooth while providing antioxidants.\n\nThese snacks are not only healthy but also versatile, allowing you to mix and match according to your taste preferences!",
